2026/02/27 16:28:20 Spawning mission funky-muffin: gemini [--output-format text --resume latest --prompt Core Concept: From Selectors to Workflows
Move from a "DOM scraper" to a Web Automation State Machine. Instead of caching simple selectors, Sapsucker will cache Workflows (Action Graphs)—JSON-serializable sequences that the Extension (the "Runner") executes.

Proposed Workflow Structure
Workflows include action types like EXTRACT, CLICK, SCROLL, WAIT, and LOOP.

Discovery Mode (Agentic): If no cached workflow exists, the LLM analyzes the DOM and the goal (e.g., "Find all job URLs"). It explores pagination or "load more" buttons and outputs a JSON Workflow.

Execution Mode (Deterministic): The Runner executes the cached JSON 99% of the time without LLM intervention, ensuring speed and low cost.

Migration & Testing Plan
Phase 1: Infrastructure Lockdown
Disable All Automation: Immediately pause all cron jobs, large-scale crawls, and background worker queues.

Update Schema: Modify the database to support Workflow definitions instead of flat selector lists.

Phase 2: The "Single-Action" UI
To test this manually, we will modify the Job Boards page:

Trigger Button: Add a "Run Manual Discovery" button next to each job board entry.

Test Environment: When clicked, it kicks off a single crawl for that specific board using the new Discovery Mode.

Feedback Loop: Display the generated JSON Workflow and the extracted data in a side panel for immediate validation.

Phase 3: Action Engine Development
The Runner: Build the Extension logic to handle the new action types (CLICK, WAIT, LOOP).

The Agent: Refine the LLM prompt to identify pagination patterns and translate them into the LOOP schema.

Phase 4: Validation
Once individual manual calls work reliably, we will re-enable the scheduler one board at a time.]
